rows.title: Rise, Chosen of the Downtrodden!
rows.titleText:
This is a world of heroes - a world where anyone can make a difference! Just keep your head down, do your duty, and in three to five business lifetimes, you too might reincarnate into the right bloodline. Or get Chosen randomly by one of the Celestial Incarnae when you decide suicide by guard is the best option.

I'll level with you: when the gods and heroes of old overthrew the Titan Tyrant, they kept most of his laws on the book. Let's see what we can do about that.

objects.title: Creation
objects.text: This world is an old one, full of mysteries and magic! Though most of the mysteries are because of Heaven's spooks. Whatever your culture is, its history has been at least partially falsified to prop up the Powers That Be. When the world is under constant threat from eldritch monsters, a lot of concessions are made in the name of stability and security. Or so they say.

objects.title: Gods
objects.text: Faith is more transactional in Creation. Your worship directly empowers a god, hopefully to do their duty but usually as payment for a protection racket. Your local mob bosses are "terrestrial gods". The celestial gods live in Heaven, the city of cities. They mostly extort their lessers for drug money while all the real work managing the seasons and destiny and everything is done by five interns in a coat closet.

objects.title: The Exalted
objects.text: The human era began when the greatest of gods empowered humanity's greatest heroes to overthrow the Titans who made the world. For their victory, they were given the Creation-Ruling Mandate, to govern the physical world and all mortal creatures. However, with no oversight beyond the threat of yet another Usurpation, each successive regime has been a crapshoot. For the past several centuries, most types of Exalted have been repressed under a dominant Dragonblooded Realm, so "Exalted" and "Dragonblooded" were synonymous. It's been a few decades since the return of the almighty Solar Exalted has finally broken the dam, and other types of Exalted are now known.

objects.title: Know your place!
objects.text: Every power of Creation has established some complex theory of rightful rule based on age or some complex symbolism. This is to justify that literally all of them came to power through Usurpation. In many parts of the world, unenlightened mortals are considered spiritually lacking and ignorant. Since the return of the Solar Exalted, however, they're at least acknowledged as potential Celestial Exalts.

objects.title: Direction
objects.text:
Creation is roughly ordered into Directions based on proximity to Elemental Poles. In the center of the world is Mount Meru - the Pole of Earth - which represents and enforces stability. Moving away from the center shifts the balance toward other elemental essence, making different environments and influencing the peoples who live there.

Pick one Direction and one Region within that Direction to be your original home.

objects.title: East
objects.text: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.

objects.title: Lunar Lands
objects.text: Let's be honest - the Pole of Water is actually the least habitable to humans. Instead of stretching ourselves thin to cover this Direction which is so overwhelmingly sparse, we've made deals with Lunar Exalted groups in the West. They'll provide us with promising candidates, and in exchange, you use your world-shaping powers to raise new land masses as their social projects expand.

defaultRowText: This is a row, and inside of it, you can place choices. On both rows and choices Requirements can be placed, which will block a row from being viewed, or make the player unable to select a choice, depending on either Point-types or the Ids of other choices. Point-types can be made in Features then Manage Points. Hovering over buttons will explain what they do. The Design of the project can be changed in 'Modify Design' at the side navigation bar, and private styling for each row can be turned on in the rows Settings. Default text like this can be turned off in Features -> Manage Defaults.
